4. The above one averaged over all the builds of each plan. Now, lets get just
the latest build of each plan:

index="bamboo" AND sourcetype="Bamboo Input" AND plan.type="chain" earliest=1 AND latest=now
| dedup buildResultKey 
| sort -number | dedup plan.key       
| table projectName, plan.key, number

The critical command is sort -number - which sorts it in reverse order by the build number.
Next, with dedup plan.key we get rid of all the other builds in the plan except the latest
one.

Instead of the last table command we can plug in the eval total_build.... stuff from the
previous search to get the successful percentage of only the latest builds in each
release plan.

